feat(news): manual flip + Read more expand on the Dolladille tile

Two controls were missing, both added now.

Manual flip
- A "See photo" pill button sits inside the front face controls row,
  and a "Read text" translucent pill overlays the bottom-right of the
  back photo. Clicking either button toggles the card between front
  and back via a new data-flip-state attribute.
- Manual mode stops the auto-flip: CSS selectors on
  [data-flip-state="front"|"back"] override the animation with a
  transform so the card stays on the user-chosen face.
- Hover and keyboard focus already pause the auto-animation
  (animation-play-state: paused).

Read more / Show less
- A "Read more" pill button toggles data-expanded on the card. CSS
  removes the 3-line clamp on the body so the full paragraph is
  readable inline; the card grows, the grid handles the reflow.
- Expanding also snaps the card to the front face so the user reads
  what they expanded. Button label swaps Read more / Show less on
  each click, localised via the dictionary (data-i18n-more /
  data-i18n-less).

i18n (en / ja / fr)
- 4 new keys: news.visit_read_more, news.visit_show_less,
  news.visit_see_photo, news.visit_see_text.
- 239 -> 243 keys; parity preserved.

JS
- initFlipCards wired after initStory. It handles the flip and
  expand actions, plus the localised label swap using
  window.__CANAL_AI_I18N__ (newly exposed by init).
